WEBVTT

02:03.370 --> 02:04.405
Get the fuck away from me.

02:04.490 --> 02:06.287
- Get up.
- Get the fuck away from me!

02:06.370 --> 02:07.906
-Get the fuck up!
-What's your problem?

02:08.000 --> 02:08.989
- Get the...

02:09.080 --> 02:10.035
Okay, all right!

02:10.630 --> 02:11.619
Get in the truck!

02:13.340 --> 02:15.797
- Get in the fucking truck. Get--

02:33.440 --> 02:35.647
I'm not doing
the swim team this year.

02:36.480 --> 02:38.107
What? You love swim team.

02:38.200 --> 02:39.315
Not here.

02:39.400 --> 02:40.947
But you haven't even given it a try.

02:41.030 --> 02:42.657
You haven't done it here.

02:42.740 --> 02:43.866
- Mom!
- Charlotte--

02:43.950 --> 02:46.407
Mom!
Isn't that Dad's bike up there?

02:53.040 --> 02:54.086
Where is he?

02:54.630 --> 02:55.995
Just stay in the car.

02:57.380 --> 02:58.369
Stay in the car.

03:08.100 --> 03:09.340
Marty?

03:42.010 --> 03:43.329
Marty!

03:47.810 --> 03:49.960
Welcome to our home, Martin Byrde.

04:02.240 --> 04:04.356
In 1929...

04:05.030 --> 04:08.443
power company stole our land,
flooded us out.

04:09.040 --> 04:12.749
Snells fled up the mountains,
and started all over again.

04:13.960 --> 04:16.872
Trouble is, ain't much grows up here.

04:17.540 --> 04:20.373
Doesn't matter how much you turn the soil.

04:20.460 --> 04:21.916
It's the water.

04:22.010 --> 04:24.626
So the crop had to change.

04:24.720 --> 04:29.168
Do you know what'll grow almost anywhere
the sun shine, Martin?

04:31.810 --> 04:32.925
Let me tell you.

04:34.440 --> 04:35.680
Poppies.

04:37.770 --> 04:41.183
Sandy soil and drought, they don't care.

04:42.740 --> 04:46.107
But then, you came along...

04:47.200 --> 04:49.156
- I think, um-- I--
- You think?

04:49.240 --> 04:51.151
- Yeah...
- You think?

04:52.240 --> 04:56.279
You know, the problem we have here
is one of power.

04:56.370 --> 04:59.282
And you seem to think
you've got more of it than you do.

04:59.710 --> 05:02.042
Now, in these parts,
power comes from time.

05:02.130 --> 05:05.759
And our family,
we got a history older than anything.

05:06.220 --> 05:07.710
So if you think...

05:08.300 --> 05:11.258
that you can talk us out of getting
what we want

05:11.350 --> 05:13.807
with your pretty little words...

05:15.100 --> 05:18.854
then you have not yet understood
the purpose of this tour.

05:26.900 --> 05:31.018
You are a threat to my colony,
Martin Byrde.

05:31.120 --> 05:34.032
You have disturbed the ecology
of our delicate little system,

05:34.120 --> 05:37.954
interrupted the back end of our operation
when you took over the club,

05:38.040 --> 05:42.875
and now you have destroyed
our very means of distribution.

05:42.960 --> 05:46.088
-I don't see how I could've possibly--
-The church, Martin.

05:47.340 --> 05:48.500
The preacher.

05:49.840 --> 05:53.594
We need the preacher on the water.

05:54.390 --> 05:57.632
Certain members in his congregation
are in our employ.

05:57.730 --> 06:02.099
The lake is under patrol,
his service less so.

06:03.360 --> 06:06.067
Now, you pull that pigeon
out of the water...

06:07.280 --> 06:10.317
and suddenly our resellers are on land...

06:11.070 --> 06:14.233
and much more likely to be pulled over.

06:14.870 --> 06:16.531
And that will not do.

06:19.210 --> 06:23.544
Cease all construction on the church.

06:24.090 --> 06:25.409
I can do that next month.

06:25.510 --> 06:26.954
Uh...

06:27.590 --> 06:29.046
...but right now...

06:29.970 --> 06:33.292
my employer would be very upset--

06:33.390 --> 06:36.632
There's a photo on a table
in your living room,

06:36.720 --> 06:39.723
your family on a cable car
in San Francisco.

06:39.810 --> 06:42.096
Another one at Myrtle Beach.

06:43.060 --> 06:47.099
Across from the couch, there's a window
you keep open mostly at night,

06:47.190 --> 06:52.560
not 15 feet from your boy's bedroom,
up the hall on the right.

06:53.320 --> 06:55.322
And your girl's just after that.

06:56.290 --> 06:59.282
And yours, Byrde, is at the very end.

06:59.370 --> 07:01.076
Your toothbrush is blue.

07:02.960 --> 07:05.167
We know all about you, Martin.

07:06.590 --> 07:09.002
We know you work for someone dangerous...

07:10.130 --> 07:11.961
and perhaps we can't touch you...

07:13.300 --> 07:15.632
or else we risk retaliation.

07:17.180 --> 07:18.636
We also know...

07:19.520 --> 07:23.308
that you left Chicago
quicker than a heartbeat.

07:23.860 --> 07:25.816
So, personally, I'm inclined to believe

07:25.900 --> 07:28.687
that you're on the outs
with your employer...

07:29.320 --> 07:32.107
and us taking care of you
might be doing him a favor.

07:32.200 --> 07:34.737
So if this little tour hasn't
done the trick,

07:34.820 --> 07:38.233
then we will enforce our demands
In a more roundabout way,

07:38.330 --> 07:40.958
by our backup plan.

07:42.670 --> 07:44.160
Pastor Mason Young...

07:44.960 --> 07:47.497
and his lovely, pregnant wife...

07:49.210 --> 07:50.666
Gracie June.

07:53.430 --> 07:54.579
Okay.

07:55.550 --> 07:56.881
Okay.

07:58.180 --> 08:02.264
The construction will never finish.

08:04.400 --> 08:05.685
That's the game.

08:06.230 --> 08:10.735
Okay? And your pastor can stay
on the water indefinitely.

08:10.820 --> 08:11.809
Does that work?

08:14.820 --> 08:18.199
We don't want another nail.

08:18.660 --> 08:24.030
We don't want another screw
In those two acres.

08:25.170 --> 08:27.912
We see so much as a cross goin' up...

08:30.050 --> 08:33.372
and we will cut that baby out
with a paring knife.

08:40.600 --> 08:42.420
-Marty!
-Dad?

08:44.310 --> 08:45.299
Marty?

08:46.480 --> 08:48.607
Call the Blue Cat, see if he's there.

09:04.120 --> 09:05.951
Rachel hasn't seen Dad all day.

09:06.040 --> 09:08.873
Okay, kids, I need you
to go to your room right now!

09:11.300 --> 09:13.450
- I'm calling 911.
- No, no. Charlotte?

09:13.550 --> 09:17.293
Charlotte, please, honey,
just go to your room, all right?

09:25.140 --> 09:27.802
Dad. He's here.
He's here, Mom.

09:30.020 --> 09:32.102
I don't know what kind of shape
the bike's in.

09:32.190 --> 09:34.181
He just came out of nowhere
and he just kept going.

09:34.280 --> 09:35.850
He might not have realized he hit me.

09:35.950 --> 09:37.349
Hey, honey. I'm okay.

09:38.030 --> 09:40.612
I'm here now. I'm okay.

09:42.030 --> 09:43.827
Oh, my God, your leg.

09:43.910 --> 09:45.650
Yeah, it's gross, but, uh,

09:45.750 --> 09:48.628
you know, fortunately, Sue Ellen, uh,
Todd's wife, was passing by...

09:48.710 --> 09:50.450
-Yeah?
-...and she gave me a ride home.

09:50.540 --> 09:52.167
-Oh, good.
-Which was really nice of her.

09:52.250 --> 09:53.330
But we beat you.

09:55.550 --> 09:56.539
What's that?

09:56.970 --> 09:58.460
But we beat you here.

09:59.180 --> 10:00.420
You weren't there when we passed,

10:00.510 --> 10:03.001
so you must have already
been with Mrs. Becker.

10:03.510 --> 10:05.057
But we beat you here.

10:06.520 --> 10:09.648
-Um... Thanks.
-Mm-hmm.

10:11.020 --> 10:13.147
Uh, right. Yeah, no,
she got lost on the way here,

10:13.230 --> 10:14.561
and I wasn't paying attention.

10:14.650 --> 10:17.528
- We're just glad you're all right.
- Yeah.

10:24.660 --> 10:25.945
Lord help you...

10:27.040 --> 10:29.326
if you eat all my Pringles.

10:29.710 --> 10:31.621
What do you got, like, a date?

10:33.630 --> 10:35.757
Shut it, Wy.

10:38.130 --> 10:38.960
Hey.

10:40.340 --> 10:41.216
You look nice.

10:43.010 --> 10:44.386
Thanks.

11:01.160 --> 11:02.559
Hi, Daddy.

11:10.040 --> 11:12.281
I mean, what the fuck
kind of place is this?

11:12.370 --> 11:15.999
You know? Those people? They're gonna
cut a human out of another human?

11:16.090 --> 11:17.910
Not if we do what they want.

11:18.010 --> 11:19.659
You know, they've been in this house.

11:19.760 --> 11:21.716
-They know which windows we keep open.
-What?

11:21.800 --> 11:24.291
They know the photos that we have,
the color of my toothbrush.

11:24.390 --> 11:26.176
What the fuck are they doing
inside our house?

11:26.260 --> 11:27.420
Casing us. What do you think?

11:28.060 --> 11:31.473
The good news is that we're safe because
they're hedging that I'm untouchable,

11:31.560 --> 11:32.936
but bad news is I'm not.

11:33.020 --> 11:34.100
But they think you are?

11:34.190 --> 11:35.680
-Yeah. For now.
-Okay.

11:35.770 --> 11:38.739
I mean, Wendy, they...
they had a gun at my back.

11:38.820 --> 11:39.889
Another one on my head.

11:39.990 --> 11:41.855
Seen too many fucking guns
the last three months.

11:41.950 --> 11:43.815
-Seen too much blood--
-The kids are safe.

11:43.910 --> 11:45.821
You and I are safe.

11:47.120 --> 11:49.497
-But we have to fix this.
-I know.

11:51.040 --> 11:54.373
Every time I check the money,
there's less of it.

11:55.710 --> 11:59.043
The stacks are half
of what they were a month ago.

11:59.760 --> 12:01.296
So move on 'em.

12:03.220 --> 12:06.098
That cash isn't worth
the paper It's printed on

12:06.180 --> 12:07.807
if I don't know how to clean it.

12:07.890 --> 12:10.381
You're the smartest person
this side of the Mississippi.

12:10.980 --> 12:14.802
Anything you don't know yet,
you'll figure.

12:18.820 --> 12:21.436
-It's just, I don't... I...
-It's just what?

12:23.110 --> 12:25.317
--Just you never done it before?

12:26.870 --> 12:30.328
Huh. First times can be fun, you know.

12:30.410 --> 12:35.245
There's a... tingle that happens
right before you do it.

12:36.170 --> 12:41.870
Do you ever watch those nature shows?
The cheetahs and the gazelles and...

12:43.010 --> 12:44.830
It's natural selection, Ruth.

12:45.510 --> 12:48.638
A moron's a different species
than you and me.

12:49.260 --> 12:51.387
We got a right to take 'em out.

12:51.470 --> 12:52.459
This guy...

12:53.560 --> 12:55.221
he's a downright numbskull

12:55.310 --> 12:57.801
for leaving that shit under his bed
to begin with.

12:57.900 --> 12:59.106
You agree?

13:02.400 --> 13:05.392
-You agree?
-Yeah, I agree. I think you're right.

13:05.990 --> 13:08.117
A lot of accidents happen on the lake.

13:09.660 --> 13:11.537
Look for opportunity.

13:12.450 --> 13:15.408
Find the scenario you can control...

13:16.120 --> 13:20.033
and you do what nature intended.

13:26.130 --> 13:29.008
Hey. You'll be fine, Ruthie.

13:30.010 --> 13:31.921
You got me inside you.

13:43.730 --> 13:44.810
Check this.

13:49.030 --> 13:50.236
Holy shit.

13:50.700 --> 13:51.689
Good?

13:54.290 --> 13:56.611
You could sell this.

13:56.710 --> 13:58.416
-Serious?
-Mm-hmm!

13:58.500 --> 14:00.877
I mean, you got the eyes
in the exact right spot.

14:00.960 --> 14:02.871
You tapered the edges.

14:03.380 --> 14:05.701
Guys would spend
five or six bucks for that.

14:05.800 --> 14:07.290
Some suckers, a lot more.

14:07.380 --> 14:11.293
Well, they... they could buy
a factory fly for 30 cents,

14:11.390 --> 14:13.176
do the job just fine.

14:13.260 --> 14:14.966
--Why they buy that?

14:15.060 --> 14:19.144
Because rich people are always looking
for new ways to spend their money.

14:21.150 --> 14:22.515
-Okay.
-Hey.

14:23.860 --> 14:24.849
Listen...

14:25.610 --> 14:30.149
I've been thinking about opening a shop
down here for a while now.

14:30.240 --> 14:34.574
Bait and tackle.
Sell two-handed rods, waders...

14:34.660 --> 14:36.241
...all kinds of gear.

14:36.330 --> 14:38.571
Hand-tied flies like this.

14:39.580 --> 14:43.414
What would you say
about coming in with me on this?

14:45.250 --> 14:46.706
You and me in business?

14:47.880 --> 14:48.869
Why not?

14:50.180 --> 14:51.465
We'd be stuck.

14:54.060 --> 14:56.346
- So?

14:56.430 --> 14:59.593
No, man. I mean, we'd need...
we'd need capital.

14:59.690 --> 15:01.009
It'd cost a lot up front.

15:01.100 --> 15:02.647
No. It doesn't have to be a big place.

15:02.730 --> 15:05.437
We could operate in cash, so we don't
have to pay credit card fees.

15:05.520 --> 15:07.226
Still, all that inventory, the rent...

15:07.320 --> 15:10.642
What about that guy
your niece works with? Byrde?

15:10.740 --> 15:12.810
-Yeah, get him to invest.
-Not him.

15:12.910 --> 15:15.822
Why not? He seems to be throwing down
on a lot of places.

15:17.120 --> 15:18.610
No. I mean, he just...

15:20.580 --> 15:22.116
Actually, you know... you know what?

15:22.210 --> 15:23.074
Hmm?

15:23.880 --> 15:26.337
Real soon I might, uh,

15:26.420 --> 15:28.957
have some of my own money
to put into this thing.

15:31.470 --> 15:34.712
God, never use your own money
on a venture.

15:35.350 --> 15:38.808
Business manager,
he told me that, once, in a Starbucks.

15:39.890 --> 15:42.381
Byrde, he's better.

15:42.480 --> 15:45.688
We could make a business plan...

15:46.770 --> 15:49.318
get Ruth to make an introduction.

15:50.690 --> 15:54.319
Hmm? Come on. Come on with me.

15:54.410 --> 15:56.025
- Hmm?
- Get back. Stop it.

15:56.120 --> 15:58.441
Oh, no, no, no. Okay. Okay.

16:01.710 --> 16:03.280
--All right.

16:04.420 --> 16:05.626
All right?

16:06.630 --> 16:09.292
I mean, we can...
we can go to Splitz tomorrow.

16:10.880 --> 16:12.336
Talk to my niece.

16:14.550 --> 16:18.884
It turns out_ that the lot isn't
zoned for a religious establishment.

16:18.970 --> 16:20.096
-Mason?
-Yeah?

16:20.180 --> 16:22.808
You're gonna get your church. I promise.
We're gonna sort this out.

16:22.890 --> 16:26.769
But... until then, there just can't be
any more construction, okay?

16:26.860 --> 16:30.432
Not by you, or me, or the crew.
No one.

16:31.320 --> 16:34.858
Good news is that you can
get right back out on the water...

16:35.450 --> 16:36.656
preaching the good word.

16:38.490 --> 16:40.902
"Everything is difficult
before it is easy."

16:43.160 --> 16:45.367
- I finished it this morning.
- Right.

16:45.460 --> 16:47.280
Figured you'd want it back
in your private library.

16:47.380 --> 16:49.587
Wouldn't believe
the late fees they charge.

16:50.170 --> 16:51.546
I haven't seen you around.

16:52.010 --> 16:54.626
Yeah. You know, uh... work.

16:54.720 --> 16:57.132
-Hey, Wyatt.
-Yeah?

16:57.220 --> 17:00.132
Got some fiberglass work
on the Lucas boat.

17:01.560 --> 17:02.549
Oh, hey.

17:03.230 --> 17:05.551
-Hi.
-Yeah. Dad, just give me a second.

17:05.640 --> 17:06.800
All right.

17:08.060 --> 17:10.221
Hey, well, it was, uh...
it was really good to see you.

17:10.320 --> 17:11.435
Yeah.

17:12.940 --> 17:14.316
Oh, yeah, Charlotte.

17:14.400 --> 17:16.561
Fl' party is this weekend.

17:16.660 --> 17:18.616
-What's that?
-Fuck the Tourists.

17:18.700 --> 17:21.533
It's a big locals' thing.
Celebrates the end of summer.

17:22.200 --> 17:23.189
Oh. Uh...

17:24.080 --> 17:26.537
Sounds cool, I guess. You know, I...

17:26.620 --> 17:27.860
Not your scene.

17:28.540 --> 17:29.700
Sorry. Just...

17:31.000 --> 17:32.046
Sorry.

17:39.010 --> 17:41.137
All right, hand me that patch kit.

17:44.730 --> 17:45.845
It's not you, you know.

17:46.690 --> 17:49.181
-What?
-That girl...

17:50.400 --> 17:51.810
She just doesn't know who she is yet.

17:53.900 --> 17:56.061
I mean, without the church,

17:56.150 --> 17:58.311
we're back to the Blue Cat and the club,
and I just...

17:58.410 --> 18:01.277
I don't know if those two can handle
the rest of it, you know?

18:01.700 --> 18:04.999
- You'll make it work.
- Yeah, what if I can't? What then?

18:05.950 --> 18:07.110
We run.

18:08.040 --> 18:09.701
We put the kids in the car, and we run.

18:09.790 --> 18:11.337
You know, we do need money. We do.

18:11.420 --> 18:14.548
We need money.
We need clean money in our name.

18:14.630 --> 18:18.259
All of our personal assets are wrapped up
in that goddamn bulldozed house

18:18.340 --> 18:19.671
and the church lot.

18:19.760 --> 18:21.216
-We're fucked.
-Okay.

18:21.300 --> 18:23.461
-Look, you just focus on Del's money...
-Yeah.

18:23.560 --> 18:26.097
-...and I'll worry about ours. Okay?
-Yeah.

18:27.680 --> 18:28.556
Good luck.

18:35.320 --> 18:37.948
This has been the best quarter
you've had in seven years, Sam.

18:38.030 --> 18:39.315
- Yeah.
- Your sales,

18:39.410 --> 18:41.310
they're up 43% from last August.

18:41.410 --> 18:44.573
I mean, while the regional comps,
they're down 6%.

18:44.660 --> 18:47.868
I mean, and the only real difference
you've made in your...

18:47.950 --> 18:51.204
in your business model,
over the last year, is me.

18:51.290 --> 18:53.451
Well, my mom puts in
the extra time, too, though.

18:55.090 --> 18:57.160
Sam, I have to redo everything she does.

18:57.260 --> 18:59.251
I know, but she still puts in the time.

19:00.630 --> 19:02.040
I deserve a bonus.

19:02.550 --> 19:05.212
The_se cookies are awful.
DId you bake these?

19:05.310 --> 19:08.017
Eugenia, would you mind terribly if...
if we just finished up here?

19:08.100 --> 19:10.091
Yes, I would. We're about to open.

19:11.400 --> 19:14.392
Okay. Wendy, go ahead.
What were you gonna say?

19:16.320 --> 19:17.639
Since I've been working with you,

19:17.730 --> 19:21.109
you've been able to increase
your commission from 5 to 7%.

19:21.200 --> 19:22.940
Now, I did some math.

19:23.030 --> 19:28.445
And you've been able to have
an additional earnings of $192,000.

19:28.540 --> 19:29.905
I think it's only fair

19:30.000 --> 19:33.288
that I should request a bonus
beyond my hourly,

19:33.380 --> 19:36.588
that will align my total compensation
with my value.

19:36.670 --> 19:37.955
--Okay.

19:39.420 --> 19:40.796
What are we talking?

19:42.760 --> 19:44.466
Half your increase in income.

19:44.970 --> 19:46.176
Half?

19:48.310 --> 19:49.174
Oh.

19:49.680 --> 19:51.307
And, you know, if you don't agree,

19:51.390 --> 19:54.359
I thank you for everything,
and you know, I'll just go...

19:54.440 --> 19:56.897
I'll go right on over to, uh,
to Lakeview Realty.

19:56.980 --> 19:58.527
-I'll see what they can offer me.
-No.

19:58.610 --> 19:59.599
Mom, just...

19:59.690 --> 20:02.318
Okay. Okay. I'll give you 10,000.

20:02.740 --> 20:03.855
Forty.

20:03.950 --> 20:06.908
That coupled with my salary
will be a little less than a third

20:06.990 --> 20:09.493
of your additional profits, give or take.

20:10.040 --> 20:11.655
-Take. With you.
-Okay. Mom.

20:11.750 --> 20:14.787
This hussy comes in here,
bats her eyes

20:14.880 --> 20:18.088
and gets your money gone faster
than a toupee in a hurricane.

20:18.170 --> 20:20.877
You know, I think I'll just go on
and do it, ï¬nally.

20:20.960 --> 20:24.509
Change my will.
Give my money to the ASPCA.

20:24.590 --> 20:27.172
Save a stray cat,
since that's what you're doing.

20:27.800 --> 20:28.960
Mom...

20:29.390 --> 20:31.597
Goddamn it.

20:34.810 --> 20:37.859
25,000.
And you take care of the open house today.

20:40.860 --> 20:41.929
Mom...?

21:08.050 --> 21:09.130
Yeah, listen, Ruth,

21:09.220 --> 21:11.552
I'm gonna be coming by tomorrow afternoon
with my contractor.

21:11.640 --> 21:12.959
We're gonna reroof the club

21:13.060 --> 21:15.346
and we're gonna do a little work
in the employees' lounge.

21:15.440 --> 21:17.761
No. We just redid the employee lounge.

21:17.850 --> 21:19.647
I'm gonna need a ride afterwards.
They need...

21:19.730 --> 21:22.062
They need another van
to help expedite the work,

21:22.150 --> 21:23.435
so I'm just gonna leave them mine.

21:24.490 --> 21:25.559
